.name
ResetHandler
.type
OS Utility
.short
Installs a reset handler
.description
Installs a handler in the keyboard.device reset handler list that is called
when you press CTRL-Amiga-Amiga. It opens a window and counts down from
9 to 0 in ten seconds and then resets the machine. This gives the machine
extra time to do vital things like validating disks, and gives you time to
reconsider the reboot.
.version
1.0
.date
1991.10.28
.author
Stefan Becker
.restrictions
Does not function on A500 or A2000A
.requirements
Requires WB 2.04 (V37) or higher\n
